What's your experience in R?: R is a maddeningly addictive language. If you loved programming and thrills in dating data, it's difficult not to cave in to the buzz around R in the last few years. I am not the typical formally-trained statistician, I am not even a follower of the cult of p-value. But I am who I am: a mere mortal with a passion for statistical thinking in dissecting a problem. With the thousands of packages (constantly updated) to choose from, R presents a unique, even if quirky, environment for digging into contemporary statistical analysis. My journey into R began with a somewhat potpourri of terrible fears due to the steep learning curve I've heard a zillion times, but after a few weeks of throat clearing, the relish of working in R soon relegate the fear to God's know where. I have never looked back since then. And I don't intend to.
I've been using R since 2010 and it has never failed to surprise me.
